storyInfo: Tuye looks to dig a well in a parched town, but the way the situation unfolds far outstrips her expectations.

attributes.text:
Mother embraces the whole Moon and weeps,
Sun tyrant rains blazing rage,
Swallows her silvery shining hair and calm bright face.
Hear Moon, hear Child, she can only open her arms,
And return you to endless blue cold under the sky.

Her murmuring tears sink into the sand,
Become crystals big as stars.
Shaped like her eyes of despair see,
The faraway view of behind,
View of behind forever embedded in the sky.

—The Lady Who Stole the Moon

attributes.content: (Rubbing eyes) What's going on? What's happening... Why the sudden stop?
attributes.name: Tuye

attributes.content: Sorry to wake you up, Tuye. A woman just ran in front of us carrying a child, so I had to slam the brakes.
attributes.name: Field Operator

attributes.content: You didn't hit them?
attributes.name: Tuye

attributes.content: No, I braked in time, but I think she's holding... a bowl?
attributes.name: Field Operator

attributes.content: What?
attributes.name: Tuye

attributes.content: Miss, water... *cough* *cough* *cough* My child has gone two days without water. Take pity, spare me a little water.
attributes.name: Grimed Woman

attributes.content: Lady, if you want water, just ask. You're not afraid of getting roadkilled jumping in front of every car coming by?
attributes.name: Tuye

attributes.content: Miss, have some heart, we have no choice. Just give us some water.
attributes.name: Grimed Woman

attributes.content: Tuye, look at how cracked the child's lips are... Dehydration's about to get her.
attributes.name: Field Operator

attributes.content: Hey, lady, take these waterskins.
attributes.name: Tuye

attributes.content: Th-That many?
attributes.name: Field Operator

attributes.content: Relax, I left enough for you. I can always cut back when necessary.
attributes.name: Tuye

attributes.content: Well, I'm not reassured!
attributes.name: Field Operator

attributes.content: Whatever, you heard me, it's fine.
attributes.name: Tuye

attributes.content: If I remember right, there's a town nearby. You two from there?
attributes.name: Tuye

attributes.content: Yes, right.
attributes.name: Grimed Woman

attributes.content: What's happened out there?
attributes.name: Tuye

attributes.content: Two years of drought, not one drop of rain in town.
attributes.name: Grimed Woman

attributes.content: And the well?
attributes.name: Tuye

attributes.content: All dry. All we draw is sand, yellow sand.
attributes.name: Grimed Woman

attributes.content: ...And your local official never did a thing? Even under such severe conditions?
attributes.name: Field Operator

attributes.content: We count ourselves lucky he didn't pack up and run like everyone else. What more can we hope for him to do?
attributes.name: Grimed Woman

attributes.content: Okay, so, what exactly do you think's so hard about living somewhere else?
attributes.name: Tuye

attributes.content: It's hard to leave home... I'm not just saying that, either. The young unmarried ones can pick up and go, but where's a woman like me going to go when I have a family to raise?
attributes.name: Grimed Woman

attributes.content: Sorry... that was rude.
attributes.name: Tuye

attributes.content: Haha, it's okay. Maybe it'll rain if we just make it to next year.
attributes.name: Grimed Woman

attributes.content: You sure about that?
attributes.name: Tuye

attributes.content: Rain always comes, sooner or later.
attributes.name: Grimed Woman

attributes.content: Sooner or later, as long as it's in time.
attributes.name: Tuye

attributes.content: Ha. Our lives are full of poor opportunities. How can we demand the rain to be in time?
attributes.name: Grimed Woman

attributes.content: Nazir, remind me what date we need to rendezvous with the landship?
attributes.name: Tuye

attributes.content: Not for a while, at least a month. We got the mission done early.
attributes.name: Field Operator

attributes.content: Then how long can we stick around here?
attributes.name: Tuye

attributes.content: Half a month at most.
attributes.name: Field Operator

attributes.content: Mm. Good enough.
attributes.name: Tuye

attributes.content: (Hops out)
attributes.name: Tuye

attributes.content: Lady, wherever your town lies, you lead the way.
attributes.name: Tuye

attributes.content: What's your plan exactly, Tuye?!
attributes.name: Field Operator

attributes.content: Dig a well!
attributes.name: Tuye

attributes.content: What?
attributes.name: Field Operator
Tuye
attributes.content: I SAID,

attributes.name: Tuye
attributes.content: I'M GONNA DIG A WELL!
The whole town's been a wreck since we got here. Wasn't expecting the mayor's place to still be in such stylish shape.
attributes.name: Field Operator

attributes.content: You weren't?
attributes.name: Tuye

attributes.content: I... you've got a point. If we can't see the funding, something else has to be footing the bill.
attributes.name: Field Operator

attributes.content: Hmph...
attributes.name: Tuye

attributes.content: Tuye, watch out!
attributes.name: Field Operator

attributes.content: Are you blind, girl?! Now what? You spilled it everywhere! My family needs that water to drink!
attributes.name: Seething Old Lady

attributes.content: Sorry, sorry, she didn't do it on purpose.
attributes.name: Field Operator

attributes.content: Okay, easy, old girl. If I give you this waterskin, are we cool?
attributes.name: Tuye

attributes.content: Take it. My fault for not looking.
attributes.name: Tuye

attributes.content: Are you really just giving me this, stranger? If you peddled it in town, you could make at least seven coins.
attributes.name: Seething Old Lady

attributes.content: Seven? You're kidding, right? I'm sorry, you're not getting seven out of this even if you count the skin.
attributes.name: Tuye

attributes.content: It took me five coins for just this jar. A waterskin as clean as yours would definitely be worth more.
attributes.name: Seething Old Lady

attributes.content: (Squats down, examines the water left in the earthen shards)
attributes.name: Tuye

attributes.content: Can you even drink stuff this filthy?
attributes.name: Tuye

attributes.content: Do you think we have a choice, girl?
attributes.name: Seething Old Lady

attributes.content: Sorry to keep you waiting, Miss Tuye. The mayor will see you now.
attributes.name: Mayor

attributes.content: Ha, you're here to see that asshole? I can only wish you good luck, then.
attributes.name: Seething Old Lady

attributes.content: What does that mean, old lady? Hey! Old lady!
attributes.name: Field Operator

attributes.content: Hey. Quit shouting, Nazir, she's gone!
attributes.name: Tuye

attributes.content: Hello, Miss Tuye, I'm the mayor of this town. I'd to welcome you on behalf of the townsfolk, haha.
attributes.name: Mayor

attributes.content: Hello there. No handshake necessary.
attributes.name: Tuye

attributes.content: Haha, I see you're full of personality. Jamil, won't you serve our honored guests some water?
attributes.name: Mayor

attributes.content: Miss Tuye, Mr. Nazir, for you.
attributes.name: Mayor

attributes.content: (Takes a gulp without hesitation)
attributes.name: Tuye

attributes.content: (Tuye, are you sure this water's safe to drink? It's all muddy and yellow like it was in the jar.)
attributes.name: Field Operator

attributes.content: We realize you may be put off by the impurity in your cups, but please, we mean no offense. To be quite honest with you, it's the only well water we could find in the village.
attributes.name: Mayor

attributes.content: If you've got water to drink, why are your townspeople risking their lives out in the waste to beg passing cars for it?
attributes.name: Tuye

attributes.content: It was my grandfather's private well, opened for a hefty sum in the rear garden when he was young. This source has always been exclusive to our family, and we never normally share it with outsiders.
attributes.name: Mayor

attributes.content: And what part of this situation is normal?
attributes.name: Tuye

attributes.content: Right. Of course, as the mayor, I can't just look after myself in times of duress, so I opened it up to the townsfolk to use last year, but...
attributes.name: Mayor

attributes.content: *cough* Wells are limited. The more you use, the less there is, and naturally... the more expensive it becomes.
attributes.name: Mayor

attributes.content: Which is how we get five gold coins for one jar of water?
attributes.name: Tuye

attributes.content: (Crushes a fly upon the desk)
attributes.name: Mayor

attributes.content: Pfah. We live in desert. What could be more valuable than water?
attributes.name: Mayor

attributes.content: (How brazen.)
attributes.name: Field Operator

attributes.content: My secretary reports that the two of you are here just to dig a single well?
attributes.name: Mayor

attributes.content: Correct. Breaking ground and sinking a well is never a small deal, so we made sure to pay a visit to the local authority beforehand.
attributes.name: Field Operator

attributes.content: It'd be a great boon to this town, and as the mayor, I'm naturally endlessly grateful to you for the efforts you'd devote to it, but, and it pains me to say this, I cannot give you permission.
attributes.name: Mayor

attributes.content: Why not? You just said it'd be a good thing!
attributes.name: Field Operator

attributes.content: Have you ever heard of The Lady Who Stole the Moon?
attributes.name: Mayor

attributes.content: Good luck finding a Sargonian who hasn't.
attributes.name: Tuye

attributes.content: You can trace this town's history back a century, to when an explorer came here to found it.
attributes.name: Mayor

attributes.content: Those gems as big as stars are buried right beneath us, as he records in his personal letters.
attributes.name: Mayor

attributes.content: Legends may be legends, but mayor after mayor has safeguarded those gemstones from being sullied by strangers' hands, as is our mission.
attributes.name: Mayor

attributes.content: Especially strangers that look to start excavating the moment they arrive in our town.
attributes.name: Mayor

attributes.content: Well, my opinion is only dumbasses would believe in that story.
attributes.name: Tuye

attributes.content: Does the truth care if it's believed in?
attributes.name: Mayor

attributes.content: You—!
attributes.name: Tuye

attributes.content: Nazir, we're out.
attributes.name: Tuye

attributes.content: Slow down, Tuye. Wait for me!
attributes.name: Field Operator

attributes.content: Bluggh—
attributes.name: Tuye

attributes.content: Tuye, a—are you alright?! Was it that water just now?
attributes.name: Field Operator
Tuye
attributes.content: Okay... murky yellow well water's usually a sign of excess iron and manganese content, but...

attributes.name: Tuye
attributes.content: Ulk, euuggh—
Tuye!
attributes.name: Field Operator

attributes.content: ...I'm fine. But I got no kind of iron tang from the water just now.
attributes.name: Tuye

attributes.content: You don't mean...?!
attributes.name: Field Operator

attributes.content: Those impurities weren't just there... they got mixed in.
attributes.name: Tuye

attributes.content: Allaenat lak, you didn't need to actually drink it.
attributes.name: Field Operator

attributes.content: Did. I bet they guard the hell out of that well. Only way I had to confirm my guess.
attributes.name: Tuye

attributes.content: So what now?
attributes.name: Field Operator

attributes.content: Find a spring to tap first, then we talk.
attributes.name: Tuye

attributes.content: Nazir, you need more body in you. Haven't been walking for half a day yet.
attributes.name: Tuye

attributes.content: *huff*... *huff* Sure, but... but it takes so much work to walk through sand. My feet just sink and sink.
attributes.name: Field Operator

attributes.content: Forgot you and I were different... Need a drink?
attributes.name: Tuye

attributes.content: I'm fine, just give me a moment's rest.
attributes.name: Field Operator

attributes.content: C'mon. We hold out for a little more, get behind that rock face up ahead, and then we rest. You're gonna dehydrate in no time flat with the sun beating down on you.
attributes.name: Tuye

attributes.content: Say... didn't you like sharing your umbrella with people?
attributes.name: Field Operator

attributes.content: You are a prime dumbass. Get over. You wanna keep getting baked?
attributes.name: Tuye

attributes.content: Ngh... okay, alright!
attributes.name: Field Operator

attributes.content: No, forget it, you look kind of worse for wear, Tuye.
attributes.name: Field Operator

attributes.content: Come on. We'll talk problems when we're over there.
attributes.name: Tuye

attributes.content: *glug* *glug*—Almost died of thirst there. Aren't you gonna sit and take a break after walking so long?
attributes.name: Field Operator

attributes.content: 270 degrees of mountain here. Forms a scoop in the topography. Favors collecting groundwater. Shade, too, so it's held onto easier once a well's dug.
attributes.name: Tuye

attributes.content: Is there anything you can't do...? Where'd you get all this knowledge about digging wells from?
attributes.name: Field Operator

attributes.content: Family upbringing. We each get trained in desert survival. Finding water sources is a mandatory course.
attributes.name: Tuye

attributes.content: What kind of family are you from? Everyone learns all this...?
attributes.name: Field Operator

attributes.content: Major traveling merchant clan. Desert wanderers, living makers.
attributes.name: Tuye

attributes.content: Oh, the trading company run by that Forte family... Should've worked it out a long time ago.
attributes.name: Field Operator

attributes.content: Quit playing it up. My parents are a branch of a branch on the family tree. You'd be surprised how distant we are. Still no getting past the old guys' family rules, though.
attributes.name: Tuye

attributes.content: Haha, never hurts to learn something new, though. Could always come in handy one day, right?
attributes.name: Field Operator

attributes.content: Oh, found you... Hey, Nazir, catch!
attributes.name: Tuye

attributes.content: Gah! What the hell's this?!
attributes.name: Field Operator

attributes.content: Haha! Chill, it won't bite you.
attributes.name: Tuye

attributes.content: It's just... it's so ugly.
attributes.name: Field Operator

attributes.content: Hey, don't knock it for its looks. Without its help, my folk'd be drowned six feet under the sand. This bug means we're not far from a spring.
attributes.name: Tuye

attributes.content: Help me out here. Turn over these stones. See if there's any greyish-yellow grass growing underneath. Blades should be tiny and thin.
attributes.name: Tuye

attributes.content: Got it, let me take a look.
attributes.name: Field Operator

attributes.content: Found it! I can't believe it... So now what?
attributes.name: Field Operator

attributes.content: Lemme see, lemme see its roots...
attributes.name: Tuye

attributes.content: Roots are more developed pointing north. We'll look that-a-way.
attributes.name: Tuye

attributes.content: Didn't think there'd be anyone around but us. What's this timber doing staked all over the place?
attributes.name: Field Operator

attributes.content: Most likely it's a burial site. It's not timber. They're grave markers.
attributes.name: Tuye

attributes.content: ...You're right. There's writing carved into these posts if you look close.
attributes.name: Field Operator

attributes.content: 'Here lies a loving father, a devoted husband and a brave soldier—Bulis Shahid Numan al-Din.'
attributes.name: Field Operator

attributes.content: '...Our beloved daughter... Latifa Numan al-Din.'
attributes.name: Field Operator

attributes.content: 'Wise elder... wayfinder... Al-Muttalib Numan al-Din.'
attributes.name: Field Operator

attributes.content: Looks like a Numan al-Din family's buried here.
attributes.name: Field Operator

attributes.content: Numan al-Din... why's that sound so familiar?
attributes.name: Tuye

attributes.content: Now you mention it, something tells me I've seen it before too.
attributes.name: Field Operator

attributes.content: ...Pfff, I remember now.
attributes.name: Tuye

attributes.content: That piece of crap mayor's place had a family tapestry up, and that was the exact name on it. Numan al-Din.
attributes.name: Tuye

attributes.content: (Winded) You don't mean...
attributes.name: Field Operator

attributes.content: Yep. The spring we're looking for is right where the bones of that guy's ancestors lie.
attributes.name: Tuye

attributes.content: Allaenat...
attributes.name: Field Operator

attributes.content: Here I was thinking we could just open a well here anyway, and what the hell could he do about it?
attributes.name: Field Operator

attributes.content: I guess it's pretty clear now... I was naive.
attributes.name: Field Operator

attributes.content: (Grabbing at bangs) Don't look at me. Not like my ideas are any better than yours.
attributes.name: Tuye

attributes.content: How about... How about we just call it quits?
attributes.name: Field Operator

attributes.content: *sigh*...
attributes.name: Field Operator

attributes.content: Miss Tuye, Miss Tuye, do you still remember me?
attributes.name: Grimed Woman

attributes.content: Um, sure do, lady. You need more water? I've still got some, just one sec and I can hand it over.
attributes.name: Tuye

attributes.content: (Shakes head) No, I'm here to return your waterskin. Thank you for being so generous.
attributes.name: Grimed Woman

attributes.content: ...It's alright.
attributes.name: Tuye

attributes.content: By the looks of your troubled faces, digging the well must not be going smoothly.
attributes.name: Grimed Woman

attributes.content: (Reluctantly nods)
attributes.name: Tuye

attributes.content: Return to your own business, Miss Tuye. Leave this place. As long as he's around, you won't be able to do anything.
attributes.name: Grimed Woman

attributes.content: You can look at what he's stuck on that wall if you don't believe me.
attributes.name: Grimed Woman
Field Operator
attributes.content: That's some crowd around it. I can't see anything.

attributes.name: Field Operator
attributes.content: Could you make way? Just let me through, please.

'We reiterate... digging unapproved wells is strictly forbidden in this town. To any who partake in such work, 20 lashings. To any who draw water, 10 lashings.' How can this bloodthirsty son of a brute—!
attributes.name: Field Operator

attributes.content: I wanna pry his chest right open and see what the hell he's got in there.
attributes.name: Tuye

attributes.content: Not a speck of conscience, at least.
attributes.name: Field Operator

attributes.content: He taxes us for every coin he can, all to one day pay a tribute to a lord ameer and be rid of this place.
attributes.name: Grimed Woman

attributes.content: He's been after it for half his life. He'd never turn a blind eye to anyone interfering with his wealth or career.
attributes.name: Grimed Woman

attributes.content: You're not from here, so he can't do anything to you, but all those who live here are subject to his bidding.
attributes.name: Grimed Woman

attributes.content: (Grinds teeth)
attributes.name: Tuye

attributes.content: I'm going home, Miss Tuye. You get some rest too, and do it soon. Before long, the sun will be rising.
attributes.name: Grimed Woman

attributes.content: Your child? How's she?
attributes.name: Tuye

attributes.content: Ah... I buried her with her grandmother.
attributes.name: Grimed Woman

attributes.content: What?!
attributes.name: Tuye

attributes.content: You were right. What's most important is being in time.
attributes.name: Grimed Woman

attributes.content: Are you alright, Tuye?
attributes.name: Field Operator

attributes.content: (Knitting her brows) Nazir, we're out of alternatives.
attributes.name: Tuye

attributes.content: (Removes pendant from her own neck)
attributes.name: Tuye

attributes.content: You take this, and run an errand for me.
attributes.name: Tuye

attributes.content: No, no, I don't need you to compensate me.
attributes.name: Field Operator

attributes.content: It's not compensation. I want you to bury it where we went yesterday—remember to take off the cord and silver ring—then chip a few marks into it.
attributes.name: Tuye

attributes.content: You know how expensive this gem is. What's your plan here?
attributes.name: Field Operator

attributes.content: The endlessly greedy will always dig their own graves.
attributes.name: Tuye

attributes.content: Tuye, what are we waiting out here for at the crack of dawn?
attributes.name: Field Operator

attributes.content: Gotta make sure we're never late. Basic manners.
attributes.name: Tuye

attributes.content: Aaaand here you are.
attributes.name: Tuye

attributes.content: You're sure you heard right? The woman found the gem right here, on this spot?
attributes.name: Mayor

attributes.content: I checked three times over, sir. It's true, it was right here. She was sheltering from the wind when she happened to see it, just buried in the sand with a corner poking out.
attributes.name: Mayor

attributes.content: That's a rare sight, I'll tell you. Seems that poem was on the mark. There really are valuables buried underground here.
attributes.name: Mayor

attributes.content: Gems as big as stars! If you offer those to the lord ameer, they'll promote you up without question.
attributes.name: Mayor

attributes.content: Brought your shovel?
attributes.name: Mayor

attributes.content: Got it right here. But, sir, why didn't we bring more people? How long will the two of us be digging here for?
attributes.name: Mayor

attributes.content: Moron! I'd be disgraced if the story got out that I dug up my own family's tomb!
attributes.name: Mayor

attributes.content: Right, right, right, the less that know, the better, understood.
attributes.name: Mayor

attributes.content: Now get to it!
attributes.name: Mayor

attributes.content: Me?
attributes.name: Mayor

attributes.content: Who else?
attributes.name: Mayor

attributes.content: Uh, yes, yessir.
attributes.name: Mayor

attributes.content: Pardon me, father, mother. I will be thankful for your blessings.
attributes.name: Mayor

attributes.content: Pardon me, grandfather, grandmother. I will be thankful for your blessings.
attributes.name: Mayor

attributes.content: *cough* *cough* *cough* Why's all this dust turning out white? *spit* *spit*
attributes.name: Mayor

attributes.content: Have you dug something up?
attributes.name: Mayor

attributes.content: No, I've dug all over, but there's nothing in here at all.
attributes.name: Mayor

attributes.content: Useless! Move, I'll do it! Damn the consequences!
attributes.name: Mayor

attributes.content: (Ferociously thrusts shovel in)
attributes.name: Mayor

attributes.content: At first, right where the tip of the shovel struck, only a mere spurt of bubbles and slurry emerges.
But very rapidly, more and more of the spring water stowed underground breaks the surface, throwing splash after splash out on the sand, sides frothing and foaming, permeating through the grains.
The ground beneath the mayor's feet begins to give and give. The secretary, sensing something is awry, quickly pushes aside the still-befuddled mayor.
In an instant, the surging spring gushes forth, a fountain of water perfectly high and straight, busting through the entire burial site.
A curtain of water, meters tall, scatters its droplets back to the surface, where they cohere into a clear stream, crossing over the sandy hills, flowing to the town far away.
What the hell is...
attributes.name: Mayor

attributes.content: Water?! There's nothing but water!
attributes.name: Mayor

attributes.content: Where are they?! Where are the gemstones?!
attributes.name: Mayor

attributes.content: I don't believe it—keep—keep digging, you! Go! I command you!
attributes.name: Mayor

attributes.content: Mayor, that's out of the question. I'd drown if I tried.
attributes.name: Mayor

attributes.content: What's that noise?!
attributes.name: Mayor

attributes.content: It's the townspeople cheering.
attributes.name: Tuye

attributes.content: Excuse me?
attributes.name: Mayor

attributes.content: Not that I can blame you for asking. Not like their voices ever made it to your ears.
attributes.name: Tuye

attributes.content: (Staring at Tuye in a daze) Why are you here?
attributes.name: Mayor

attributes.content: I'm here to congratulate you, Mr. Mayor. You gotta understand, no treasure in the desert's more precious than water.
attributes.name: Tuye

attributes.content: (Hopelessly wipes water off face)
attributes.name: Mayor

attributes.content: Got what you wanted. You must be one happy man.
attributes.name: Tuye

attributes.content: You—it was you—
attributes.name: Mayor

attributes.content: (Shrugs)
attributes.name: Tuye

attributes.content: You dare do me like this! Those destitute husks put you up to it, didn't they! Didn't they?!
attributes.name: Mayor

attributes.content: You won't get away with this! Every last one of you, I'll make your lives a living hell!
attributes.name: Mayor

attributes.content: You've got some fluster on display. How's it taste, nurturing a dream for years just for it to shatter overnight?
attributes.name: Tuye

attributes.content: Okay, fine, I'll give you an out.
attributes.name: Tuye

attributes.content: Didn't hesitate to go find water for your townsfolk, even if you had to damage your ancestors' graves. That's a meritorious deed if I ever heard one. You report it to the lord ameer, Mr. Mayor, and you get a transfer to wherever the hell you want.
attributes.name: Tuye

attributes.content: Still, though...
attributes.name: Tuye

attributes.content: Still, no matter how rich your town, no matter how much dignity you scrounge up, you'll be nothing but a bloodsucking tick your whole life!
attributes.name: Tuye

attributes.content: I've already sent a letter out, for your commendation and recommendation. Lord ameer's envoy should be here in less than a month.
attributes.name: Tuye

attributes.content: You still wanna get out of here, I say you seize the opportunity, treat your townsfolk well, and turn your reputation around, fast.
attributes.name: Tuye

attributes.content: It's your very last chance.
attributes.name: Tuye

attributes.content: You... you...
attributes.name: Mayor

attributes.content: Not gonna get your mayor outta here, Mr. Secretary? Look at how dumbstruck he is.
attributes.name: Tuye

attributes.content: We're out, Nazir. We've done everything we need to.
attributes.name: Tuye

attributes.content: Tuye...
attributes.name: Field Operator

attributes.content: Nazir? You wanna keep up with me or not?
attributes.name: Tuye

attributes.content: Look, Tuye. A rainbow. There's a rainbow in the sunshine.
attributes.name: Field Operator
